Abilities, task and activities a patient has limitations doing.
Human processes or metabolic rutes the protein is involved in. The ids and names are terms from the Gene Ontology.

These are drugs with a biological origin. This term includes vaccines, blood components, allergenics, somatic cells, gene therapies, tissues, recombinant therapeutic protein, and living cells used in cell therapy.
Location of a cell where the protein is located. The ids and names are terms from the Gene Ontology.
Genetic technical term used to describe the clinical items included in the nomenclature of rare diseases. The id is ORPHAcode.
The degree to which the ability is affected in the patient.
The functional consequences of a disorder are divided into different abilities, task, and activities of the everyday life. Disability involves limitation or restriction in a task.
A disorder can be a disease, a symdrom or an anomaly.
A molecular compound that is used as a treatment for a disease involving a protein. The ids and names are from the DrugBank.
An enzyme is a protein that has catalytic activity and a metabolic pathway.
The drug is either in experimental phase, approved or withdrawn
Description of the protein function(s). The names and ids are terms from the Gene Ontology. The description is obtained from Uniprot.
A group of disorder is a set of disorder that have some properties in common.
Weather the ability is lost by the pacient over the course of a disease or not.
A protein is a biological molecule encoded by a gene. The ids and names are retrieved from Uniprot.
This type of protein usually regulates some process in the cell or binds to DNA or RNA to regulate the transcription or translation of a protein.

Low molecular weight drugs (900 daltons) which are produced by chemical synthesis. These drugs have well defined structures and chemical properties. In DrugBank, some drugs larger than 900 daltons are considered small molecule drugs (such as monomers: ribo- or deoxyribonucleotides, amino acids, and monosaccharides).
A subtype of disorder is a especific type of disorder that can be either clinical, etiological or hisotpahtological.
The symptoms and sign of a disorder are annotated with Human Phenotype Ontology terms.
Period of time the functional consequence/disability is present in the life of the patient.
A protein that can transport a molecule or group of molecules.
